## What Epochgram processes

Epochgram processes your vault data **locally on your device**. Your notes, file content, summaries, epochs, embeddings, semantic matches, and timeline data are **not sent to our servers**.

## Epochgram Pro

Epochgram Pro requires an account, payment, and internet access for license checks. During account, billing, and license validation, we may process:

- your email address;
- your license key;
- basic server-side telemetry needed for license validation, fraud prevention, and service administration.

Payments and billing may be handled by third-party providers.

## AI Bridge

If you use AI Bridge, Epochgram starts a local server on `http://127.0.0.1` and opens a local bridge page in Google Chrome to use Chrome's on-device AI APIs. The bridge communication stays on your device.

Chrome may download built-in model files the first time these APIs are used. Epochgram may also check common OS install paths to locate the Google Chrome executable and open the bridge automatically. This happens locally on your device.

## Similarity and model downloads

If you use semantic similarity or topic features, required model or runtime files may be downloaded to your device from third-party sources such as model hosts or CDNs. Those providers may receive standard request data such as your IP address and user agent when delivering files.

## Support

If you contact us, we may process your email address and any information you send us in order to respond and provide support.

## Sharing

We do not sell your personal data. We may share limited data with service providers only where needed to operate payments, licensing, hosting, support, or related infrastructure.

## Retention

We keep account, licensing, billing, and support data only as long as reasonably necessary to provide the service, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.

## Your rights

Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or object to certain processing of your personal data.

To make a privacy request, contact: **contact@epochgram.com**

